1.Given an array of strings words, return the first palindromic string in the array. If there is no
such string, return an empty string "". A string is palindromic if it reads the same forward and
backward.
Code:
def firstPalindrome(words):
  for word in words:
    if word == word[::-1]:
     return word
  return ""
print(firstPalindrome(["abc","car","ada","racecar","cool"]))

Output:
adc
